# EF Core ðŸ—„ï¸

The ORM for .NET.

Code-First approach: Write C# classes, and EF generates the SQL database schema.

```csharp
public class Blog {
    public int BlogId { get; set; }
    public string Url { get; set; }
}
```

# The Pipeline ðŸš‡

Request processing pipeline.

Requests pass through middleware components (Auth, Logging, Static Files).

```csharp
app.UseHttpsRedirection();
app.UseAuthentication();
app.MapControllers();
```

# Microservices Style âš¡

Build APIs without the MVC boilerplate.

```csharp
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
var app = builder.Build();

app.MapGet("/", () => "Hello World!");

app.Run();
```

